                                                                                                 NIST SP 800-57 PART 1 REV. 5                                               RECOMMENDATION FOR KEY MANAGEMENT:
                                                                                                                                                                                               PART 1 – GENERAL

                                                                                                 7 Key States and Transitions
                                                                                                 A key may pass through several states between its generation and its destruction. Figure 3 depicts
                                                                                                 an example of the key states that a key could assume and the transitions among them.

